angry /ˈæŋɡrɪ/

(angrier,angriest) 

1. ADJ When you are angry , you feel strong dislike or impatience about something. 生气的 

例： Are you angry with me for some reason? 你是因为某个原因生我的气了吗？ 

例： I was angry about the rumours. 我对这些谣言感到生气。 

例： An angry mob gathered outside the courthouse. 一群愤怒的民众聚集到了法院外面。 

2. angrily ADV 生气地 [ADV with v] 

例： Officials reacted angrily to those charges. 官员们愤怒地回应了那些指控。

